<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call casts a const char * (VirtualPath) to (void *) when calling OS_ObjectIdGetBySearch, discarding the const qualifier. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 which requires pointers to point to const-qualified types when possible. The correct remedy is to change the callee prototype to accept a const void * (or otherwise avoid discarding const), or ensure the argument is non-const if the function legitimately needs to modify it.
</scenario>
