explanation:
Agent A is correct. In OS_TranslatePath the call
  OS_ObjectIdGetBySearch(..., (void *)VirtualPath, &token);
casts a const char * (VirtualPath) to void *, thereby discarding the const qualifier. That hides a mismatch between the argument (const) and the callee parameter (non-const) and is exactly the kind of situation MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 aims to prevent (pointers should point to const-qualified types whenever possible). The proper fixes are to make the callee accept a pointer-to-const (e.g. change the prototype to accept const void * and update any callback/signature such as OS_FileSys_FindVirtMountPoint accordingly), or if the function legitimately needs to modify the data, change the caller so the argument is non-const. The current explicit cast is not an acceptable remedy under MISRA. Therefore the reported violation is correct.
